Class ViewInterpreter

java.lang.Object
  mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.FieldListener
      mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.ViewInterpreter
Direct Known Subclasses:
ConsumerViewInterpreter, QueryViewInterpreter, SpatiotemporalViewInterpreter, Test.TestViewInterpreter
public abstract class ViewInterpreter
extends FieldListener

A ViewInterpreter is a Fieldlistener that transforms its Fields of interest into new values in another set of output Fields. It makes the transformation in response to a query. The transformation has two inputs: the Fields of interest and the query parameters, a State other than the one that contains the Fields of interest.

Field Detail

_dirtyParameterFields

private final Set _dirtyParameterFields
The set of names of query parameter Fields that have changed. setDirtyParameterFields(List) adds Field names to _dirtyParameterFields. clearDirtyParameterFields() empties it.

getCurrentFieldValues

protected State.ChangeMessage getCurrentFieldValues(State parameters)
Builds a State.ChangeMessage that contains the current values of all output Fields. Invokes interpret(List, State) to learn some of the output Field values.

Implementation note: Ensure that the interpret(List, State) includes each output Field in its output.

Parameters:
parameters - the query parameters
Returns:
a State.ChangeMessage that contains one Field.ChangeMessage for each output Field

interpret

protected abstract State.ChangeMessage interpret(List fieldChanges,
                                                 State parameters)
Transforms the changes in Fields of interest along with the query parameters into a State.ChangeMessage that contains one Field.ChangeMessage for each changed output Field. interpret may return null. interpret may return a State.ChaneMessage with no Field.ChangeMessages inside.

Parameters:
fieldChanges - a List of Field.ChangeMessages from the Fields of interest. It may be null.
parameters - the query parameters. It may be null.
Returns:
a State.ChangeMessage containing the changes to the output Fields. It may be null or empty.

isDirty

public abstract boolean isDirty(State parameters)
This ViewInterpreter decides if it is interested in writing given the changes in its query parameters. It may consult getDirtyParameterFields().

Parameters:
parameters - the query parameters. It may be null.
Returns:
true if the ViewInterpreter is interested in writing; false otherwise

getQualifiedFieldName

public static String getQualifiedFieldName(Class classOfAViewInterpreter,

Transforms the unqualified name of a field into a qualified one. A qualified field name uniquely identifies the kind of ViewInterpreter that provided it. It follows the pattern fully qualified class name_unqualified field name.
